My Vim Configuration
====================
:Author:    Kalkin Sam
:Email:     mail@kalkin.de
:Date:      2010-09-15
:Revdate:   2010-09-15 


Information 
-----------
My vim configuration uses pathogen and git submodules to properly handle the
plugin chaos. This configuration was first based on Christian `strcat`
Schneiders vim configuration http://github.com/strcat/dotfiles


Building Vim
~~~~~~~~~~~~
I always edit src/features.h file before compiling vim. I remove farsi,
rightleft, arabics, emacs_tags and lispindent features. This way I can build a
huge vim package without the strange stuff you never need. 

Also I don't use any sort of GUI with vim, I use --enable-gui=X11, because this
way I get some nice features. See :h +xterm_clipboard and :h +X11 for more
information. 

I also enable ruby interpreter for using the snipmate plugin


 
Configure
^^^^^^^^^
--------------------------------------------------------------
./configure --with-compiledby='Kalkin Sam' --enable-gui=X11 \
    --with-features=huge --enable-rubyinterp
--------------------------------------------------------------

